==Trivia==
*In the comics, Thena was born '''Azura''', but her name was changed to resemble more the Greek goddess of Strategy and War, {{WPS|Athena}}. She mothered a son, [[w:c:marvel:Joey Eliot (Earth-616)|Joey]], with a [[human]], [[w:c:marvel:Thomas Eliot|Thomas Eliot]]. She is also the daughter of [[w:c:marvel:Zuras|Zuras]], and cousin of [[Thanos]].
*In the comics, Thena had a long relationship with General [[Kro]] and had two sons with him, [[w:c:marvel:Deborah & Donald Ritter (Earth-616)|Donald Ritter]] and [[w:c:marvel:Deborah & Donald Ritter (Earth-616)|Deborah Ritter]].

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Angelina Jolie]] signed up to play Thena in ''[[Eternals (film)|Eternals]]'' because of her desire to support [[Chloé Zhao]]'s vision and [[Marvel Studios]]' commitment to expand the way audience see superheroes nowadays.<ref>[https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/angelina-jolie-interview “I’ve Come Through A Few Things. I’m Trying To Be Hopeful”: At Home With Angelina Jolie]</ref>
*[[Katie McDonnell]] and [[Kimberly Shannon Murphy]] were stunt doubles for [[Angelina Jolie]] in the role of Thena.
*[[Caridad Angus]], [[Amber Coyle]] and [[Ruth Horrocks]] were stand-ins for [[Angelina Jolie]] in the role of Thena.

